00:55:17.560 --> 00:55:20.150
So what are the
policy challenges?

00:55:20.150 --> 00:55:22.810
One is the markets are
readily susceptible to fraud

00:55:22.810 --> 00:55:24.550
and manipulation.

00:55:24.550 --> 00:55:26.440
Any market-- it's human nature.

00:55:26.440 --> 00:55:29.500
I don't think we're going to
take the human out of human.

00:55:29.500 --> 00:55:32.200
It's going to look for
angles, look for ways to make

00:55:32.200 --> 00:55:35.470
opportunities, even
the best meaning folks.

00:55:35.470 --> 00:55:39.760
If you hold the assets in
custody and you might make

00:55:39.760 --> 00:55:43.630
the markets, because you're
not settling to the blockchain,

00:55:43.630 --> 00:55:46.450
even for short whiles
, this market model,

00:55:46.450 --> 00:55:50.710
this business model is
to make markets maybe.

00:55:50.710 --> 00:55:52.540
There's inherent
conflicts of interest.

00:55:52.540 --> 00:55:55.930
There's conflicts of interest
in pretty much all of finance.

00:55:55.930 --> 00:55:57.280
But then we try to manage.

00:55:57.280 --> 00:55:59.080
We either manage
conflicts of interest

00:55:59.080 --> 00:56:02.530
by certain rules about
transparency or certain

00:56:02.530 --> 00:56:05.240
prohibitions about,
in the custody world,

00:56:05.240 --> 00:56:07.480
banks hold custody as well.

00:56:07.480 --> 00:56:10.630
But we prohibit them
from using your assets

00:56:10.630 --> 00:56:12.910
unless you permission
them to use your assets,

00:56:12.910 --> 00:56:14.630
and things like that.

00:56:14.630 --> 00:56:17.140
So what we try to
use usually is build

00:56:17.140 --> 00:56:22.330
some system of transparency and
affirmative responsibilities

00:56:22.330 --> 00:56:25.870
or prohibitive actions, those
three buckets, transparency,

00:56:25.870 --> 00:56:27.940
some affirmative
responsibilities,

00:56:27.940 --> 00:56:31.570
and prohibited actions
around conflicts.

00:56:31.570 --> 00:56:34.150
But this space has the
conflicts without much

00:56:34.150 --> 00:56:36.640
of those three
things, transparency,

00:56:36.640 --> 00:56:41.050
either obligations or
prohibitive actions.

00:56:41.050 --> 00:56:43.460
So inevitably, I think
it's human nature.

00:56:43.460 --> 00:56:48.100
You're going to have some
kind of games going on.

00:56:48.100 --> 00:56:52.300
The custodial arrangements we
talked about, big challenge.

00:56:52.300 --> 00:56:55.530
We're going to see a
little bit more about that.

00:56:55.530 --> 00:56:58.380
Complying with anti-money
laundering, KYC,

00:56:58.380 --> 00:57:00.750
and implementing tax reporting.

00:57:00.750 --> 00:57:05.120
In the US, at least,
in the US, brokers

00:57:05.120 --> 00:57:08.810
have to report to the
government when you buy and sell

00:57:08.810 --> 00:57:10.510
something.

00:57:10.510 --> 00:57:13.030
This was not true
30 and 50 years ago.

00:57:13.030 --> 00:57:15.850
But we've come to
a place where I

00:57:15.850 --> 00:57:20.050
think it was in the last 15
to 20 years, laws changed.

00:57:20.050 --> 00:57:22.010
Ross, maybe you know
on your legal work.

00:57:22.010 --> 00:57:25.240
