But how do you come
into compliance?

01:03:52.935 --> 01:03:54.560
And so that will be
an interesting sort

01:03:54.560 --> 01:04:00.710
of what level of regulatory
forbearance will there be?

01:04:00.710 --> 01:04:02.480
I think that at
some point in time,

01:04:02.480 --> 01:04:05.550
there will be fines
and penalties.

01:04:05.550 --> 01:04:09.840
But I think in the US context,
they'll bring a half a dozen,

01:04:09.840 --> 01:04:13.110
or eight, or 10 into regulation.

01:04:13.110 --> 01:04:18.090
And then they'll bring
down a heavier footprint,

01:04:18.090 --> 01:04:22.710
bring down the hammer, if
you wish, in 2019 or 2020.

01:04:22.710 --> 01:04:24.810
I don't think that's
going to be in 2018.

01:04:24.810 --> 01:04:25.665
Kelly?

01:04:25.665 --> 01:04:28.387
AUDIENCE: So maybe this is
a question for Thursday,

01:04:28.387 --> 01:04:33.090
but what is the thought on
the side of the exchanges?

01:04:33.090 --> 01:04:36.555
Do you think that there
will be a huge cost to them

01:04:36.555 --> 01:04:38.040
to come into compliance?

01:04:38.040 --> 01:04:41.010
Or do they think that
they're going to lose members

01:04:41.010 --> 01:04:44.600
or maybe even it would increase
because it's [INAUDIBLE]??

01:04:44.600 --> 01:04:47.730
PROFESSOR: So a
very good question.

01:04:47.730 --> 01:04:52.230
What does being compliant with
some broad public policy norms

01:04:52.230 --> 01:04:52.730
do?

01:04:52.730 --> 01:04:55.370
And I think there's probably
different business models.

01:04:55.370 --> 01:04:57.350
If you're an incumbent,
like NASDAQ--

01:04:57.350 --> 01:04:59.080
and there was a
brief article when

01:04:59.080 --> 01:05:00.920
Adena Friedman who
runs NASDAQ said

01:05:00.920 --> 01:05:02.550
she wanted to be in this space.

01:05:02.550 --> 01:05:04.970
If you're NASDAQ, if
you're CME, if you're

01:05:04.970 --> 01:05:08.660
Deutsche Borse in
Germany, if you're ICE,

01:05:08.660 --> 01:05:11.880
you really already know
how to be compliant.

01:05:11.880 --> 01:05:16.340
It's probably advantageous
to be registered

01:05:16.340 --> 01:05:19.130
and for all those
startups to be registered.

01:05:19.130 --> 01:05:21.470
In some ways, it creates
a barrier to entry.

01:05:21.470 --> 01:05:23.270
But you want to do it.

01:05:23.270 --> 01:05:26.340
If you're a startup, you
could go one of two paths.

01:05:26.340 --> 01:05:30.350
So Gemini here in the US and
Coinbase, at least publicly,

01:05:30.350 --> 01:05:32.097
are saying we want
to be compliant.

01:05:32.097 --> 01:05:32.930
How do we get there?

01:05:32.930 --> 01:05:34.550
Coinbase may be,
because now they're

01:05:34.550 --> 01:05:37.190
almost like an incumbent.

01:05:37.190 --> 01:05:42.770
And so they might want to keep
the next round of startups out.

01:05:42.770 --> 01:05:45.320
But I think around
the globe, there's

01:05:45.320 --> 01:05:47.540
no doubt that it
would raise costs.

01:05:47.540 --> 01:05:51.860
The question is whether it would
either secure your market share

01:05:51.860 --> 01:05:55.660
or flush out some competitors.

01:05:55.660 --> 01:05:57.520
I would contend that
it would increase

01:05:57.520 --> 01:05:59.740
the overall size of the market.

01:05:59.740 --> 01:06:02.260
Because more people
would be interested.

01:06:02.260 --> 01:06:05.080
But some fear that it
would shrink the market.

01:06:05.080 --> 01:06:09.070
Because if you had known
beneficial ownership,

01:06:09.070 --> 01:06:10.660
if you tracked
beneficial ownership

01:06:10.660 --> 01:06:16.000
for 100% of this market, some
worry the market would shrink.

01:06:16.000 --> 01:06:18.290
That's from a
commercial concept.

01:06:18.290 --> 01:06:21.470
Meaning, if you're tracking
beneficial ownership.

01:06:21.470 --> 01:06:22.220
Question Riham?

01:06:22.220 --> 01:06:25.670
AUDIENCE: [INAUDIBLE] the whole
