between individuals
without having

01:06:34.310 --> 01:06:36.920
regulations, this
more libertarian

01:06:36.920 --> 01:06:41.362
view of exchanges [INAUDIBLE].

01:06:41.362 --> 01:06:43.070
PROFESSOR: So the
nature of your question

01:06:43.070 --> 01:06:48.230
is, isn't Bitcoin and crypto
about some off the rails,

01:06:48.230 --> 01:06:51.800
libertarian, pro
libertarian, peer to peer?

01:06:51.800 --> 01:06:53.150
I think it's genesis.

01:06:53.150 --> 01:06:54.610
Eric, you want to answer?

01:06:54.610 --> 01:06:56.456
AUDIENCE: [INAUDIBLE]
there's common theme

01:06:56.456 --> 01:06:59.220
in the reading
about Coinbase where

01:06:59.220 --> 01:07:02.660
[INAUDIBLE] the fact
that more and more people

01:07:02.660 --> 01:07:04.610
with that libertarian
point of view

01:07:04.610 --> 01:07:07.550
are constantly reminded
[INAUDIBLE] that it's

01:07:07.550 --> 01:07:09.860
kind of betraying that ideal.

01:07:09.860 --> 01:07:13.750
But you don't have
to believe me.

01:07:13.750 --> 01:07:17.220
I mean, he's trying to make
a business out of this.

01:07:17.220 --> 01:07:19.650
So being compliant
with that is actually

01:07:19.650 --> 01:07:22.070
trying to broaden
the base of customers

01:07:22.070 --> 01:07:26.640
and make the business more
profitable and growth.

01:07:26.640 --> 01:07:31.170
PROFESSOR: I think that to
go from a $200 billion market

01:07:31.170 --> 01:07:33.480
to $2 trillion or
$10 trillion, it's

01:07:33.480 --> 01:07:36.330
got to come inside the
public policy envelope.

01:07:36.330 --> 01:07:41.810
I just don't see particularly,
lowering the risk

01:07:41.810 --> 01:07:44.270
of manipulation and fraud.

01:07:44.270 --> 01:07:48.320
Then you're going to have a
broader societal acceptance.

01:07:48.320 --> 01:07:50.900
And investor protection matters.

01:07:50.900 --> 01:07:54.950
But there are others on
the other side of that.

01:07:54.950 --> 01:07:56.040
These are on the numbers.

01:07:56.040 --> 01:07:57.207
I'm not going to stay on it.

01:07:57.207 --> 01:07:59.630
But this is just
to say one thing

01:07:59.630 --> 01:08:03.170
Crypto Compare does is
average daily visitors

01:08:03.170 --> 01:08:04.870
